# Build and run `if-else` parser

bison -d if_else.y
flex if_else.l
gcc if_else.tab.c lex.yy.c -o ifelse -lfl

./ifelse

Then paste an if-else snippet like `if (x > 0) { y = 1; } else { y = -1; }` and press Enter.

If you get a missing-header error in `if_else.l` (e.g., `y.tab.h`), ensure `bison -d` is run first. If header names differ, update the `#include` in the lexer to match the generated header (e.g., `if_else.tab.h`).
